[Why can the health officals not confirm or deny anthrax through tests on
critically ill patients? - Mod.TG
[In SE Asia anthrax is more common in buffalo and pigs than elsewhere in
the world. However, the number of people sick, 268, would be a record for
enteric anthrax or even a mixture of cutaneous cases ("red spots"?) among
the butchers plus enteric cases among the diners. The usual case numbers
for "severe" outbreaks is in the range of 1-3 dozen people, maximum. In
Muslim countries autopsies are usually frowned upon, which can severely
limit the quality of their data. Logically, though, there should be
adequate opportunities for suitable sample collection from the sick. - MHJ
